{
  "text": "There was an inverse correlation between sphere size in vitro and trichogenicity in vivo at a population level, as CD133\u00c0 spheres formed the largest spheres and largely failed to induce hair follicles in vivo, whereas Sox2 \u00fe cells were least proliferative in vitro and made the greatest contribution to the dermis in vivo. The inverse relationship between proliferation and trichogenicity may also contribute to the www.jidonline.org 1089 loss of DP activity when cells are grown in 2D cultures [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Sphere size in vitro did not determine hair follicle type in vivo, at least in the presence of unfractionated P2 dermal cells, as the proportion of awl/auchene and ZZ hair follicles was similar in Sox2 \u00fe CD133 \u00fe and Sox2\u00c0CD133 \u00fe grafts. We can conclude, however, that the presence of Sox2 \u00fe spheres is not inhibitory to ZZ hair formation.",
